loration of current trends in media industries from diverse perspectives. Within the framework of understanding contemporary and future trajectories in media markets and industries, the volume delves into their influence on media organization and delivery, along with broader societal and market implications. Encompassing research at the crossroads of economics, management, political economy, and production studies, the handbook emphasizes the necessity for a robust interdisciplinary dialogue. Beyond scrutinizing present and forthcoming industry developments, the handbook addresses pivotal issues pertaining to media economics research methods and pedagogy. It serves as a valuable resource for scholars, students, and media professionals, providing insights into media economics as an academic field and delving into the multifaceted dynamics that shape the media landscape. Doing this, it contributes to the ongoing discourse on the evolving nature of media markets and their profound impact on society.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aMass mediaxEconomic aspects. 4aKommunikation. 4aMedienindustrie. 4aMedienkonzerne. 4aMedienmanagement. 4aMedienökonomie.  aMedia economics.  amedia firms.  amedia industries.  amedia management.  amedia markets.  amethods.1 aAllam, Rasha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBallon, Pieter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBertoni, Carolina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBhargav, Nimmagadda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrown, Charles, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBudzinski, Oliver, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCabañes, Jason, e